<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">March 10, 2025</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-march-10-2025/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-250528 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Screenshot-2025-03-07-at-3.16.10 PM-150x150.png" alt="the great gatsby" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.vox.com/culture/402406/great-gatsby-f-scott-fitzgerald-centennial-100" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">100 years of (rereading) </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">The Great Gatsby</span></i></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.theparisreview.org/blog/2025/03/07/for-gary-indiana-1950-2024/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Sam McKinniss on Gary Indiana</span></a></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400"><a href="https://www.newyorker.com/books/book-currents/jeremy-denks-musical-account-of-american-divisions" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Books about the relationship between music and politics</span></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-march-10-2025/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
